# Switching to Gnu+Linux
#### 12-06-2021

After a very, very long time... I've finally switched to gnu+linux full time ! Since I have a laptop that runs an Nvidia 1050Ti, I've switched to @[PopOS](https://pop.system76.com/)(to escape the hell that is Nvidia driver management). It's a very liberating feeling, especially since I've been wanting to do this forever. No more Windows, no mode WSL (it's not bad, but it does feel a little clunky), no more mingw nonsense or even worse, MSVC and Visual Studio nonsense ! No more weird issues with no fixes online.

Now I'm finally in the land of fixable problems xD, coz don't get me wrong, @[Ubuntu](https://ubuntu.com/)has its own share of weird issues. But since the community has been good so far, I don't anticipate unfixable problems in the near future. Looking forward to this new life ! xD
